<br>
I realize people are concerned about twinking but I sure wish I could play more than one character on the FV server.  I have 4 accounts as it is, so obviously, twinking is a possibility for me regardless.  The only people that 1-character-per-account rule really hurts are the people who can't afford more than 1 account and having to buy expansions for all the accounts.<br>
<br>
I have a friend who wants to try other classes but really doesn't care for the non-roleplay servers either.<br>
<br>
Oh well, there's always the option to turn off ooc/shout/auction or filter them to a window that isn't a bother. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dalninil@firionavie>Dalninil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 782<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/4/02 11:45:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3209.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: An unexpected side effect of the FV server</span><hr size=1> the reason for the single character per account thing is rather simple.<br>
<br>
the big negative to the server ? TLC <br>
so if i could have 8 characters i can pretty much cover any mob i wanted with a character. And with no drop removed that would mean alot of ultra twinks with no want to level. so named spawn instead of being farmed by high level mages druids etc  would now be  farmed by X level 32 alt in Ntov or better gear. not that that doesn't happen but the extra 12$ a month limits it a bit. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=caillougna>Caillou GNA</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.tshrew.net/caillou/Caillou-sm.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 858<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/4/02 1:41:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3209.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.tshrew.net/caillou/Caillou-sm.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: An unexpected side effect of the FV server</span><hr size=1> At this point in time, I wouldn't be surprised if the majority (can be as little as 51%) of the server population has at least one extra account.  Though, out of those that have 2 or more accounts, I would hazzard a guess than a lot less than half dual-box or hydra even if they can (as in have the computers to do so).  The $13 a month isn't the bad part (heck, that's dinner out for 1 person in most large urban areas), it's the initial cost of the software in a lump sum.<br>
<br>
But, yeah, I, too, find it hard to even contemplate going back to a different server.<br>
