<br>
After reading countless accounts of players experiences on other servers it seems like we play a completely different game here on FV than everyone else does. The attitudes, childishness and general stupidity that seems to be the norm on the other blue servers is almost nonexistant or at least greatly diminished here. Even the Uber guilds on this server are for the most part made up of descent people.<br>
<br>
Well enough babbling from me for today. <br>
<br>
PoBorblefoot <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=urhofv>UrhoFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/5/02 3:09:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3209.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> chars</span><hr size=1> Honestly I do believe that the rule of 1 char per 1 account contributes a _lot_ to the general level of maturity in the server. Which then can been seen on general player behavior /ooc's /shouts etc etc.<br>
<br>
Even if you have 2 accounts to play 2 chars, you still have to take care of their reputation to get along in the long run. Totally different from having full regular set of chars which will cause few effects: <br>
<br>
1.) same amount of players playing as a lot more toons, so it'll be harder to remember people you meet as faces keep changing all the time. means don't have to watch out for the reputation so much.<br>
<br>
2.) can always switch chars if you fool/grief around<br>
<br>
3.) level of RP will drop a *LOT* ... who's gonna be having energy to RP all the toons while switching back and forth?<br>
<br>
I do think this rule is one of those things which is foundation to the uniqueness of the whole server. It's easier to see it's negative side (can't make a nother toon without another account)...<br>
<br>
Remove this rule and TLC and say Hi! to million powergaming dewds running in to enjoy the low population and non no drop stuffs etc etc... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xenojones>XENOJONES</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 604<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/5/02 5:19:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3209.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: chars</span><hr size=1> TLC is gone essentially with the new raid format and to be honost TLC being lifted would not affect this server in a bad way regardless. Sure a few druids around 40th would lose their farmage of glowing worm bile, but who really cares. <br>
<br>
I do like the limited number of toons people have available. Keeps people a little more focused on their main character instead of fighting over all the bank uberloot that is starting to pile up in the Reso banks <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<br>
