<br>
I also started EverQuest on Firiona Vie due entirely to the &quot;(Roleplaying Preferred)&quot; next to the server name.  On a couple of occasions, I've tried other servers, and my experiences with them were uniformly bad.  I hadn't been playing for ten minutes on a blue server before some jerk came up to me, insisted that I duel him for money, and then trained a monster over to kill me when I declined.<br>
<br>
I often wish I could have a second character on Firiona Vie, as I never seem to be able to settle on one character, but I think the server would lose something major if they started allowing multiple characters.<br>
<br>
I AM glad that they relaxed the naming rules... sort of.  While I'm all right with banning a few of the most well-known names in fantasy/sci-fi literature, there are just too many names out there which someone could object to.  I've had names rejected because they apparently belonged to some obscure fantasy character I'd never encountered.<br>
<br>
I tend to prefer having single-name characters with a real-sounding last name - Frost, Pryce, Graves, etc.  The prior naming restrictions wouldn't allow my current character to have his name.  On the flipside, I wince when I see someone with a surname like Rollinfatties.<br>
<br>
Anyway, for those who think Firiona Vie is a mature server now... you shoulda seen it before the rules were relaxed.  Man, it scared off d00ds quickly.  Now I run into a few here and there.  Still nothing like blue servers; still wouldn't play EverQuest anywhere else.<br>
<br>
What saddens me about EQII is that I don't see them making an equivalent of Firiona Vie...<br>
-Graves<br>
Shaman of the Tribunal<br>
Wearer of Ten Medicine Bags<br>
Clan of Brothers <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ralgur>Ralgur</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/6/02 12:07:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3209.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: chars</span><hr size=1> Trust me, I would rather be limited to one character per account than have the server degrade into doodism.  I guess I just don't think about twinking myself.  I have 4 accounts and could do so once I get one character high enough level, but to me it destroys the fun.  Typically I'm only playing one account at a time even though I *could* play 3 at a time if I wanted.<br>
<br>
I don't really mind the TLC either.  I guess the point I was trying to get across is that some of the armor quests are really hard to get the ingredients for.  My DE necro sits around waiting for the halfling scouts to wander off alone so he can kill one to hopefully get a hide for his armor and he still hit 6th season pretty quickly.  If I don't get all the hides before they become trivial, I will have to rely on buying them.  I much prefer to earn stuff.  It means more.  Sure, the armor isn't so good but it's the accomplishment I enjoy.  My DE cleric is in full quest, my DE sk is in full quest and my necro has a couple of pieces.<br>
<br>
I surely don't want to ruin the environment on FV.  I guess some of us do the right thing regardless whereas if you give some the chance, they'll abuse things.<br>
<br>
It's fine the way it is.  I'll get my armor one way or another. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ralgur>Ralgur</A> at: 12/6/02 12:14:22 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=maushi>Maushi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/6/02 3:36:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3209.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Yep</span><hr size=1> Couldn't agree more.  The overall attitude is much more positive than on blue servers.   This coming from a middle age Spaniard.  Between the childish attitudes and the slang I didnt recognize, I just couldn't tolerate blue servers anymore. <br>
<br>
Still, I see the ocassional mindless trains who can be avoided but are not and a few other things that are easy to tolerate and perhaps just part of the game.<br>
